## Working with loops

# What is iteration?
In programming, iteration refers to the repetition of instructions or a block of code. Iterative control structures are used to carry out a block of code until some condition changes. As an example, if your objective is to flip a coin and achieve three heads in a row, you will continue to flip the coin until your objective is satisfied so that you can move onto the next task. 

